WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.936 --> 00:00:10.375
<i>Previously on</i> From...

2
00:00:10.417 --> 00:00:12.057
<i>I hear their voices.</i>

3
00:00:12.099 --> 00:00:14.619
Sara. just tell me what you did.

4
00:00:14.661 --> 00:00:17.222
<i>I left the door open.</i>

5
00:00:17.264 --> 00:00:19.785
<i>I have Sara tied up in the
basement of the church.</i>

6
00:00:19.827 --> 00:00:20.986
Tell me you're joking.

7
00:00:21.028 --> 00:00:23.148
That girl may be the key
to unlocking all this.

8
00:00:23.190 --> 00:00:26.551
<i>That girl may be the
way we all go home.</i>

9
00:00:26.593 --> 00:00:28.473
Let's take a walk.

10
00:00:28.515 --> 00:00:29.714
<i>We have to turn around!</i>

11
00:00:29.756 --> 00:00:31.236
We can't be here!
Stop the bus!

12
00:00:31.278 --> 00:00:32.757
Everyone lease
return to your seats!

13
00:00:32.799 --> 00:00:34.359
Bad things are
gonna happen if...

14
00:00:36.603 --> 00:00:37.642
Stop the goddamn bus!

15
00:00:37.684 --> 00:00:39.164
Everyone on. right now.

16
00:00:39.206 --> 00:00:41.064
You're gonna get people
killed. you realise that?

17
00:00:41.088 --> 00:00:42.167
<i>Hello?</i>

18
00:00:42.209 --> 00:00:43.688
Where are you?

19
00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:45.971
<i>Is this Jim?</i>

20
00:00:46.013 --> 00:00:48.135
<i>Your wife shouldn't be
digging that hole. Jim.</i>

21
00:00:54.421 --> 00:00:57.422
You ever wonder
if Abby was right?

22
00:00:57.464 --> 00:00:59.264
What if it's all just a dream?

23
00:01:00.347 --> 00:01:02.349
Aah!

24
00:01:02.950 --> 00:01:05.510
My blood is your blood now.

25
00:01:05.552 --> 00:01:06.872
<i>Who was in my room?</i>

26
00:01:06.914 --> 00:01:08.593
Sorry? Someone was in my room.

27
00:01:08.635 --> 00:01:09.835
and they took something.

28
00:01:09.877 --> 00:01:11.036
Uh. I think I saw Jade

29
00:01:11.078 --> 00:01:12.415
and the Matthews boy
up here last night.

30
00:01:12.439 --> 00:01:13.879
You are not listening to me.

31
00:01:13.921 --> 00:01:15.818
No. I am listening. and I'm
telling you to fuck off.

32
00:01:15.842 --> 00:01:18.483
Residents don't carry
guns. That's the rule.

33
00:01:18.525 --> 00:01:21.927
Well. uh. rules change.

34
00:01:21.969 --> 00:01:23.929
The wires aren't
connected to anything.

35
00:01:23.971 --> 00:01:26.051
They were just dangling
from the ceiling.

36
00:01:26.093 --> 00:01:29.014
Tabitha. we have so
much to talk about.

37
00:01:29.056 --> 00:01:30.695
I saw something
that wasn't there.

38
00:01:30.737 --> 00:01:31.776
What?

39
00:01:31.818 --> 00:01:34.379
I saw two children

40
00:01:34.421 --> 00:01:36.743
<i>standing in the middle of
the road staring at me.</i>

41
00:01:38.425 --> 00:01:40.427
Hello? Someone down here?

42
00:01:45.352 --> 00:01:47.354
Hi. Kenny.

43
00:01:51.598 --> 00:01:55.560
And right through here
we have the common area.

44
00:01:55.602 --> 00:01:58.924
And downstairs you'll have a
nice big room all to yourself.

45
00:01:58.966 --> 00:02:00.968
Come on in.

46
00:02:03.050 --> 00:02:04.529
No.

47
00:02:04.571 --> 00:02:07.092
I don't like it here.

48
00:02:07.134 --> 00:02:08.573
It's too sunny.

49
00:02:08.615 --> 00:02:10.896
I-I want to go home.

50
00:02:10.938 --> 00:02:12.737
No. no. Dad. It's okay. look.

51
00:02:12.779 --> 00:02:14.419
Um. this place is really nice.

52
00:02:14.461 --> 00:02:16.942
And. look. there's a
perfect little spot here

53
00:02:16.984 --> 00:02:18.986
for us to play chess.

54
00:02:19.826 --> 00:02:21.828
We stay here together?

55
00:02:24.351 --> 00:02:26.952
I'll give you folks
a few minutes. okay?

56
00:02:26.994 --> 00:02:28.996
Thanks. Yeah.

57
00:02:38.245 --> 00:02:40.325
Look. Dad.

58
00:02:40.367 --> 00:02:42.807
Mom and I are gonna be
right down the street.

59
00:02:42.849 --> 00:02:45.652
You know? And we'll come
here every single day.

60
00:02:47.014 --> 00:02:49.134
But it's really. really
important for you

61
00:02:49.176 --> 00:02:52.099
to be somewhere where you
can't open the door at night.

62
00:02:55.422 --> 00:02:57.424
Dad. what happened last night...

63
00:02:58.745 --> 00:03:00.747
It's safer this way.

64
00:03:02.549 --> 00:03:04.349
No.

65
00:03:04.391 --> 00:03:05.470
I go home now.

66
00:03:28.135 --> 00:03:30.297
Uh. I'll go get the
rest of the stuff.

67
00:03:48.755 --> 00:03:50.635
Kenny.

68
00:03:50.677 --> 00:03:52.237
Sheriff Boyd. hey.

69
00:03:52.279 --> 00:03:54.281
Everything all right?

70
00:03:55.602 --> 00:03:58.803
Yeah. we were just. uh. we're
getting my dad settled in.

71
00:03:58.845 --> 00:04:00.847
I heard you had a
scare last night.

72
00:04:03.090 --> 00:04:05.092
Those things were knocking
on the door. they're...

73
00:04:06.573 --> 00:04:08.575
He was convinced that. uh.

74
00:04:09.536 --> 00:04:11.176
that his brothers were outside.

75
00:04:11.218 --> 00:04:12.257
Right.

76
00:04:12.299 --> 00:04:14.539
My mom tried to
stop him but. uh.

77
00:04:14.581 --> 00:04:16.781
he... he pushed her.

78
00:04:16.823 --> 00:04:18.825
It was. uh...

79
00:04:19.666 --> 00:04:21.668
Yeah. man. it's...

80
00:04:22.309 --> 00:04:24.429
It's hard.

81
00:04:24.471 --> 00:04:26.473
First time seeing your
parents struggle. huh?

82
00:04:29.076 --> 00:04:31.078
Yeah.

83
00:04:31.398 --> 00:04:33.400
You know. this place...

84
00:04:34.281 --> 00:04:36.721
there's not a lot
holding it together.

85
00:04:36.763 --> 00:04:39.406
You know. everyone is
scared and confused.

86
00:04:40.407 --> 00:04:42.207
but a thing I
learned in the army.

87
00:04:42.249 --> 00:04:44.569
it always helps to
have people to look to.

88
00:04:44.611 --> 00:04:46.892
people who seem like they know
what the hell they're doing.

89
00:04:47.854 --> 00:04:49.454
That's really all I'm
trying to do here.

90
00:04:49.496 --> 00:04:51.618
Seems like you're doing
a really good job.

91
00:04:54.060 --> 00:04:56.062
I could use some help.

92
00:04:56.583 --> 00:04:58.945
Wouldn't mind having a
deputy watching my six.

93
00:05:01.908 --> 00:05:03.910
What do you say?

94
00:05:04.791 --> 00:05:06.793
You think?

95
00:05:08.115 --> 00:05:09.514
I think. right?

96
00:05:09.556 --> 00:05:10.875
Uh. yeah.

97
00:05:10.917 --> 00:05:12.919
I mean...

98
00:05:16.363 --> 00:05:18.365
Sheriff Boyd!

99
00:05:19.886 --> 00:05:21.086
I have to show you something.

100
00:05:21.128 --> 00:05:22.167
Can it wait? I gotta...

101
00:05:22.209 --> 00:05:23.768
No. no. no.

102
00:05:23.810 --> 00:05:26.853
Um. I have... I have
to show you now.

103
00:07:35.342 --> 00:07:38.223
Hey. I was gonna make some tea.

104
00:07:38.265 --> 00:07:40.267
You want some?

105
00:07:41.468 --> 00:07:42.547
Are you okay?

106
00:07:42.589 --> 00:07:44.591
Hey.

107
00:07:45.272 --> 00:07:47.274
Yeah. I'm fine.

108
00:07:48.635 --> 00:07:50.995
It happened again. didn't it?

109
00:07:51.037 --> 00:07:53.039
You saw something.

110
00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:55.240
I need you to watch
Ethan for a minute.

111
00:07:55.282 --> 00:07:57.284
I need to talk to your father.

112
00:07:58.164 --> 00:08:00.447
Mom. you can tell me.

113
00:08:03.330 --> 00:08:05.812
I know. I know.

114
00:08:08.655 --> 00:08:10.535
Yes. it happened again.

115
00:08:10.577 --> 00:08:13.620
I saw something. but.
listen. I'm fine.

116
00:08:14.381 --> 00:08:16.341
And you're fine. right?

117
00:08:16.383 --> 00:08:18.583
We're good. Yeah.

118
00:08:18.625 --> 00:08:20.627
I just need to talk to Daddy.

119
00:08:22.789 --> 00:08:24.791
Okay. Okay.

120
00:08:30.116 --> 00:08:32.118
I'll be right back.

121
00:08:38.124 --> 00:08:39.724
Where's Mom going?

122
00:08:39.766 --> 00:08:40.885
Uh. she...

123
00:08:40.927 --> 00:08:42.927
Oh. Christ!

124
00:08:42.969 --> 00:08:44.971
Are you people living here now?

125
00:08:45.332 --> 00:08:46.611
Our house collapsed.

126
00:08:46.653 --> 00:08:48.733
Well... at least you had one.

127
00:08:48.775 --> 00:08:50.094
It's not my fault you broke it.

128
00:08:50.136 --> 00:08:51.816
Hey. take it easy.

129
00:08:51.858 --> 00:08:53.676
We finally get rid of those three
smelly hippies from Colony House

130
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:55.702
and now we got you people!

131
00:09:00.026 --> 00:09:01.946
Still wanna go see Victor?

132
00:09:01.988 --> 00:09:03.990
Yeah.

133
00:09:09.075 --> 00:09:11.077
When I came down earlier...

134
00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:15.402
she was here.

135
00:09:32.779 --> 00:09:34.781
Give us a minute. okay?

136
00:09:36.182 --> 00:09:37.261
What?

137
00:09:37.303 --> 00:09:39.305
I need to talk to her.

138
00:09:40.507 --> 00:09:43.029
In private. Wait
for me upstairs.

139
00:09:44.310 --> 00:09:46.030
Please. Kenny.

140
00:09:46.072 --> 00:09:48.074
I got this.

141
00:09:51.798 --> 00:09:53.800
All right.

142
00:09:56.122 --> 00:09:58.124
All right.

143
00:10:08.735 --> 00:10:10.214
I'm glad you're okay.

144
00:10:10.256 --> 00:10:13.017
Yeah. that's debatable.

145
00:10:13.059 --> 00:10:15.061
I got about a thousand
questions for you.

146
00:10:16.022 --> 00:10:17.662
What happened to you?

147
00:10:17.704 --> 00:10:19.706
After you pushed
me in that tree?

148
00:10:20.066 --> 00:10:21.506
Where'd you go?

149
00:10:21.548 --> 00:10:23.388
I followed right behind you.

150
00:10:23.430 --> 00:10:25.309
And?

151
00:10:25.351 --> 00:10:27.353
And then I was here.

152
00:10:28.074 --> 00:10:30.074
So you...

153
00:10:30.116 --> 00:10:31.636
You been here since
the other night?

154
00:10:31.678 --> 00:10:33.680
I didn't know what else to do.

155
00:10:34.360 --> 00:10:36.401
Where did you go when
you went through?

156
00:10:36.443 --> 00:10:38.445
That's a...

157
00:10:39.526 --> 00:10:41.406
How did you know?

158
00:10:41.448 --> 00:10:43.450
How'd you know
what that tree was?

159
00:10:44.971 --> 00:10:46.891
A little boy told me.

160
00:10:46.933 --> 00:10:49.454
He was standing up on the
ridge. wearing all white.

161
00:10:49.496 --> 00:10:50.855
He said that Nathan was right.

162
00:10:50.897 --> 00:10:52.737
that we made this place angry.

163
00:10:52.779 --> 00:10:54.781
but we'd be safe in the tree.

164
00:10:56.182 --> 00:10:58.302
So. this little boy. that's
one of the voices you hear.

165
00:10:59.025 --> 00:11:00.785
No.

166
00:11:00.827 --> 00:11:02.627
No. this was different.

167
00:11:02.669 --> 00:11:03.708
I think... Jesus.

168
00:11:03.750 --> 00:11:05.590
I think he's trapped
here like us.

169
00:11:05.632 --> 00:11:08.352
that he wants to help.
but he's not sure how.

170
00:11:08.394 --> 00:11:10.515
No shit.

171
00:11:10.557 --> 00:11:15.079
Look. I am glad you're back.

172
00:11:15.121 --> 00:11:17.123
I am. I am.

173
00:11:18.044 --> 00:11:20.284
But you being here.

174
00:11:20.326 --> 00:11:22.046
that's a shitstorm
waitin' to happen.

175
00:11:22.088 --> 00:11:24.208
We need to figure out
how to handle this.

176
00:11:24.250 --> 00:11:26.973
You know what you have to do.

177
00:11:28.374 --> 00:11:29.814
We're not talkin' about this.

178
00:11:29.856 --> 00:11:33.698
Boyd. it was always going to
end like this. You knew that

179
00:11:33.740 --> 00:11:35.179
when you brought me out there.

180
00:11:35.221 --> 00:11:38.503
There's no way I can
ever live here again.

181
00:11:38.545 --> 00:11:40.264
Hey.

182
00:11:40.306 --> 00:11:42.388
Just sit tight. okay?

183
00:11:43.830 --> 00:11:46.112
I gotta talk to
Kenny. Just sit tight.

184
00:11:50.797 --> 00:11:52.799
Boyd?

185
00:11:54.841 --> 00:11:56.843
You didn't tell Kenny

186
00:11:57.203 --> 00:11:59.405
'bout what happened that
night at the clinic.

187
00:12:02.488 --> 00:12:04.490
No.

188
00:12:17.904 --> 00:12:19.906
What is going on?

189
00:12:20.226 --> 00:12:22.466
Look.

190
00:12:22.508 --> 00:12:25.950
Now. I'm just gonna say
this as plainly as I can.

191
00:12:25.992 --> 00:12:31.636
Okay. Sara is uniquely
connected to this place.

192
00:12:31.678 --> 00:12:33.878
Something here has
communicated with her.

193
00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:35.079
Communicated how?

194
00:12:35.121 --> 00:12:37.321
She hears voices.

195
00:12:37.363 --> 00:12:38.723
Ye... I know.

196
00:12:38.765 --> 00:12:39.924
I know how it sounds.

197
00:12:39.966 --> 00:12:41.263
Believe me. When Father
Khatri came to me...

198
00:12:41.287 --> 00:12:43.289
Father Khatri knew?

199
00:12:43.890 --> 00:12:46.531
Father Khatri locked
her up in the basement.

200
00:12:46.573 --> 00:12:47.972
Apparently Nathan
had come to him

201
00:12:48.014 --> 00:12:49.453
earlier in the day.
he was worried.

202
00:12:49.495 --> 00:12:51.776
Thought she might do
something to hurt someone.

203
00:12:51.818 --> 00:12:53.938
So. Father Khatri
questioned her.

204
00:12:53.980 --> 00:12:55.900
and what he found proof of

205
00:12:55.942 --> 00:12:57.944
is that something here
is talking to her.

206
00:12:59.105 --> 00:13:01.746
Using her like... like...

207
00:13:01.788 --> 00:13:03.790
A pawn.

208
00:13:04.911 --> 00:13:08.673
He figured if something
here is using her.

209
00:13:08.715 --> 00:13:10.595
if she really is
connected to this place.

210
00:13:10.637 --> 00:13:13.638
then we can use
that to understand

211
00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:15.682
what this place actually is.

212
00:13:19.205 --> 00:13:21.566
Okay. I don't... So. what?

213
00:13:21.608 --> 00:13:23.930
She's just been downstairs
since Father Khatri died?

214
00:13:25.331 --> 00:13:27.572
No.

215
00:13:27.614 --> 00:13:29.616
I took her with me
into the forest.

216
00:13:30.617 --> 00:13:32.697
Jesus. I...

217
00:13:32.739 --> 00:13:34.338
Look. hey. when
push came to shove.

218
00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:36.060
she's the reason I made it back.

219
00:13:36.102 --> 00:13:38.382
That girl downstairs
saved my life.

220
00:13:38.424 --> 00:13:41.185
and I know. I know
she did bad things.

221
00:13:41.227 --> 00:13:42.707
Horrible things!

222
00:13:42.749 --> 00:13:44.869
But this place. Kenny.

223
00:13:44.911 --> 00:13:48.192
it can make you think you're
doing them for good reasons.

224
00:13:48.234 --> 00:13:50.995
She killed her own brother!

225
00:13:51.037 --> 00:13:54.198
She tried to kill a
nine-year-old kid! Yes. I know!

226
00:13:54.240 --> 00:13:55.800
Do you? Because you lied.

227
00:13:55.842 --> 00:13:57.161
You lied to everyone!

228
00:13:57.203 --> 00:13:58.482
You lied to me!

229
00:13:58.524 --> 00:14:00.084
Yeah. okay. okay.

230
00:14:00.126 --> 00:14:01.846
Okay. you're right.

231
00:14:01.888 --> 00:14:04.488
And I know that what
she did is unforgivable.

232
00:14:04.530 --> 00:14:06.771
but. listen. when she
killed those people...

233
00:14:06.813 --> 00:14:08.613
People?

234
00:14:08.655 --> 00:14:09.854
It was just Nathan.

235
00:14:09.896 --> 00:14:12.016
No. I mean. yeah.

236
00:14:12.058 --> 00:14:14.378
She almost with
the... with Ethan...

237
00:14:14.420 --> 00:14:16.422
You know what I'm
talking about. right?

238
00:14:16.863 --> 00:14:18.865
Kenny!

239
00:14:21.748 --> 00:14:23.107
Boyd.

240
00:14:23.149 --> 00:14:25.389
What's gonna happen
when everyone finds out?

241
00:14:25.431 --> 00:14:27.391
When Jim and Tabitha

242
00:14:27.433 --> 00:14:28.993
and Ethan's whole
family finds out?

243
00:14:29.035 --> 00:14:31.037
Yeah. okay. Well...

244
00:14:32.679 --> 00:14:33.998
We'll handle it.
She's dangerous.

245
00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:36.360
Boyd. she belongs in the Box.

246
00:14:36.402 --> 00:14:38.923
Okay. well. she's not dangerous.

247
00:14:38.965 --> 00:14:40.084
Not anymore.

248
00:14:40.126 --> 00:14:41.806
Okay. would you
still be saying this

249
00:14:41.848 --> 00:14:43.567
if it was Ellis that
she almost killed?

250
00:14:43.609 --> 00:14:44.689
She's not goin' in the Box.

251
00:14:44.731 --> 00:14:46.250
If we really wanna
figure this out...

252
00:14:46.292 --> 00:14:48.813
Hey. she's not going in
the goddamn Box. okay!

253
00:14:48.855 --> 00:14:52.378
No one else is going in...
into the fucking Box!

254
00:14:53.099 --> 00:14:57.421
Oh. okay. I. uh...

255
00:14:57.463 --> 00:15:00.584
I-I-I need some air.

256
00:15:00.626 --> 00:15:01.666
I gotta...

257
00:15:01.708 --> 00:15:03.710
Boyd!

258
00:15:15.802 --> 00:15:17.804
Boyd.

259
00:15:19.005 --> 00:15:20.685
I can't...

260
00:15:20.727 --> 00:15:23.527
Boyd! Boyd! Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey!

261
00:15:23.569 --> 00:15:25.571
Hey! You okay?

262
00:15:26.012 --> 00:15:27.131
Guys. come on!

263
00:15:27.173 --> 00:15:29.333
Jeez!

264
00:15:33.259 --> 00:15:35.261
Hey. Hey. slow down.

265
00:15:45.631 --> 00:15:47.111
Not too long. okay?

266
00:15:47.153 --> 00:15:49.155
Okay.

267
00:15:52.598 --> 00:15:54.600
Hey. you.

268
00:15:55.641 --> 00:15:57.361
Guess it's laundry day?

269
00:15:57.403 --> 00:15:59.846
I'm just trying to get things
back to some sense of normal.

270
00:16:02.088 --> 00:16:03.848
I never got to congratulate you

271
00:16:03.890 --> 00:16:04.929
on the engagement.

272
00:16:04.971 --> 00:16:07.011
Oh. I'm really
happy for you guys.

273
00:16:07.053 --> 00:16:10.735
Well. in that case.
maybe you'd consider

274
00:16:10.777 --> 00:16:12.616
being one of my bridesmaids.

275
00:16:12.658 --> 00:16:13.697
What?

276
00:16:13.739 --> 00:16:15.379
Ellis doesn't wanna wait.

277
00:16:15.421 --> 00:16:17.423
We're gonna...

278
00:16:18.224 --> 00:16:20.226
We're getting married here.

279
00:16:21.587 --> 00:16:22.867
Oh. my God. Seriously?

280
00:16:22.909 --> 00:16:24.228
Right?

281
00:16:24.270 --> 00:16:26.272
But I mean. it's...

282
00:16:27.593 --> 00:16:31.235
Well. I would be honoured to
be one of your bridesmaids.

283
00:16:31.277 --> 00:16:33.197
Why. thank you kindly.

284
00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:36.480
I saw the new guy outside.

285
00:16:36.522 --> 00:16:39.403
Elgin. yeah. he's. uh...

286
00:16:39.445 --> 00:16:41.447
I think he's having
a rough time.

287
00:16:42.208 --> 00:16:44.210
Maybe I could talk to him?

288
00:16:45.611 --> 00:16:47.131
Really?

289
00:16:47.173 --> 00:16:48.572
Yeah.

290
00:16:48.614 --> 00:16:50.616
It was nice having
people do it for me.

291
00:17:07.313 --> 00:17:09.315
Hi.

292
00:17:09.836 --> 00:17:11.838
What do you want?

293
00:17:12.278 --> 00:17:14.198
I was worried about you.

294
00:17:14.240 --> 00:17:15.599
I'm glad you're okay.

295
00:17:15.641 --> 00:17:17.643
Well. I'm not very
happy with you.

296
00:17:19.285 --> 00:17:20.925
Can I come in?

297
00:17:20.967 --> 00:17:23.249
I don't know. Are you
gonna steal anything else?

298
00:17:23.970 --> 00:17:25.369
I told him not to.

299
00:17:25.411 --> 00:17:26.770
I said you wouldn't like it.

300
00:17:26.812 --> 00:17:29.535
Well. you should've
said it louder.

301
00:17:38.584 --> 00:17:40.344
My mom said you helped her.

302
00:17:40.386 --> 00:17:42.388
Out in the forest.

303
00:17:43.109 --> 00:17:45.389
She's a nice lady.

304
00:17:45.431 --> 00:17:47.433
You're lucky to have
a mom like that.

305
00:17:49.155 --> 00:17:50.674
What are you drawing?

306
00:17:50.716 --> 00:17:51.956
New stuff.

307
00:17:51.998 --> 00:17:53.237
What kind of new stuff?

308
00:17:53.279 --> 00:17:55.281
Things we saw.

309
00:17:55.922 --> 00:17:56.961
You and my mom?

310
00:17:57.003 --> 00:17:59.005
Yeah. Yeah.

311
00:18:00.166 --> 00:18:01.685
Where did you guys go?

312
00:18:01.727 --> 00:18:03.407
You should go now.

313
00:18:03.449 --> 00:18:05.451
'cause I'm pretty busy.

314
00:18:07.013 --> 00:18:08.372
Well...

315
00:18:08.414 --> 00:18:10.416
Please just go!

316
00:18:14.220 --> 00:18:16.941
I found these in
the storage closet.

317
00:18:16.983 --> 00:18:18.985
I thought you might like them.

318
00:18:31.357 --> 00:18:33.359
I'm sorry I made you mad.

319
00:18:37.083 --> 00:18:39.085
Okay.

320
00:18:40.927 --> 00:18:42.929
Bye.

321
00:18:50.776 --> 00:18:52.256
Hey.

322
00:18:52.298 --> 00:18:54.300
You're Elgin. right?

323
00:18:54.981 --> 00:18:56.420
Yeah. Julie?

324
00:18:56.462 --> 00:18:58.464
Yeah.

325
00:18:59.425 --> 00:19:01.465
How's your dad?

326
00:19:01.507 --> 00:19:03.629
Uh. he's pretty beat up.

327
00:19:04.951 --> 00:19:07.431
Kristi. the doctor.
she's trying to get him

328
00:19:07.473 --> 00:19:09.475
to take it easy for a bit.

329
00:19:13.599 --> 00:19:15.479
You been here a while?

330
00:19:15.521 --> 00:19:17.523
Uh. not that long.

331
00:19:18.044 --> 00:19:20.046
Kinda feels like a lifetime.

332
00:19:25.291 --> 00:19:27.811
Look. I know you probably have

333
00:19:27.853 --> 00:19:30.093
tons of people telling you
they're here if you wanna talk.

334
00:19:31.137 --> 00:19:34.939
but I'm around if
you wanna talk.

335
00:19:34.981 --> 00:19:37.101
Believe it or not.
it actually helps.

336
00:19:38.384 --> 00:19:40.386
I appreciate that.

337
00:19:41.988 --> 00:19:43.827
Hey. what's going
on? I thought you...

338
00:19:43.869 --> 00:19:45.950
I wanna go home.

339
00:19:45.992 --> 00:19:47.994
Okay. well. ca...

340
00:19:51.917 --> 00:19:53.919
I think that's my cue.

341
00:19:54.680 --> 00:19:55.879
It was nice meeting you.

342
00:19:55.921 --> 00:19:57.923
Likewise.

343
00:19:58.764 --> 00:20:00.884
Hey!

344
00:20:00.926 --> 00:20:02.928
Ethan. wait up.

345
00:20:03.929 --> 00:20:04.969
Good.

346
00:20:05.011 --> 00:20:06.730
And then we'll do
the other hand.

347
00:20:06.772 --> 00:20:08.212
I'm telling you. I'm fine.

348
00:20:08.254 --> 00:20:10.734
I'm just tired. that's all.

349
00:20:10.776 --> 00:20:12.456
Oh. given your vast
medical training

350
00:20:12.498 --> 00:20:14.500
I guess there's nothing
to worry about. then.

351
00:20:18.064 --> 00:20:20.024
Now press up as hard as you can.

352
00:20:21.227 --> 00:20:22.946
Good.

353
00:20:22.988 --> 00:20:24.468
What about spider bites?

354
00:20:24.510 --> 00:20:28.112
I got spiders on me when
I was out in the forest.

355
00:20:28.154 --> 00:20:30.156
Uh. yeah. Let me take a look.

356
00:20:31.277 --> 00:20:32.516
Let's see.

357
00:20:32.558 --> 00:20:34.838
There's one here. Okay.

358
00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:36.882
And then there's...

359
00:20:37.683 --> 00:20:41.725
They don't look swollen or
inflamed. which is good.

360
00:20:41.767 --> 00:20:44.088
Uh. but do you wanna
tell me about this?

361
00:20:44.130 --> 00:20:46.170
What? It's nothing. I just...

362
00:20:46.212 --> 00:20:47.291
Boyd!

363
00:20:47.333 --> 00:20:49.495
I just scratched it
on a tree branch.

364
00:20:53.018 --> 00:20:55.179
It's. um... it's not infected.

365
00:20:55.221 --> 00:20:56.860
but keep it clean. okay?

366
00:20:56.902 --> 00:20:58.904
Yes. ma'am.

367
00:21:01.747 --> 00:21:04.108
Those tremors. have
they gotten any worse?

368
00:21:04.150 --> 00:21:05.709
They come and go.
I'm dealing with it.

369
00:21:05.751 --> 00:21:08.632
Have you noticed any symptoms
other than the shaking?

370
00:21:08.674 --> 00:21:09.713
Such as?

371
00:21:09.755 --> 00:21:11.955
Visual impairment.
muscle stiffness...

372
00:21:11.997 --> 00:21:13.999
Nope. Depression?

373
00:21:14.560 --> 00:21:16.480
Kristi. everybody
here is depressed.

374
00:21:19.725 --> 00:21:23.487
You know. I remember
my... my dad. he got...

375
00:21:23.529 --> 00:21:26.490
It started to mess with
his mind at the end.

376
00:21:26.532 --> 00:21:28.190
Yeah. I don't think that's
anything that you need

377
00:21:28.214 --> 00:21:29.493
to be worrying about right now.

378
00:21:29.535 --> 00:21:31.375
Cognitive impairment
with Parkinson's

379
00:21:31.417 --> 00:21:34.658
doesn't happen until way
down the line. if at all.

380
00:21:34.700 --> 00:21:36.702
Why? Is there something?

381
00:21:37.183 --> 00:21:38.822
No. Just... Just curious.

382
00:21:38.864 --> 00:21:41.145
I'm telling you. I'm fine.

383
00:21:41.187 --> 00:21:43.307
Fine.

384
00:21:43.349 --> 00:21:45.269
Okay. but you need
to rest. okay?

385
00:21:45.311 --> 00:21:46.888
In your condition.
you can't afford to be

386
00:21:46.912 --> 00:21:48.914
putting any extra stress
on your body right now.

387
00:21:56.522 --> 00:21:57.721
Boyd. what's going on?

388
00:21:57.763 --> 00:21:59.765
Nothing! I'm sorry.

389
00:22:00.886 --> 00:22:03.927
The idea that anybody
here could avoid

390
00:22:03.969 --> 00:22:06.370
putting extra stress
on anything is just...

391
00:22:06.412 --> 00:22:10.774
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

392
00:22:13.819 --> 00:22:15.018
This is great.

393
00:22:15.060 --> 00:22:17.341
Uh. not a good idea. Okay.

394
00:22:17.383 --> 00:22:19.903
Just sit. okay? Come on!

395
00:23:33.859 --> 00:23:37.182
For fuck's sake. there's literally
nowhere in this town I can be alone.

396
00:23:39.505 --> 00:23:41.507
Wait a second. You're
the bus driver. right?

397
00:23:44.230 --> 00:23:45.549
I'm sorry. It's
been a long day.

398
00:23:45.591 --> 00:23:46.968
Stay as long as you
want. all right?

399
00:23:46.992 --> 00:23:48.994
I'm just gonna...

400
00:23:54.159 --> 00:23:56.161
That boy.

401
00:23:58.003 --> 00:24:00.125
He said to me. "Turn around."

402
00:24:02.248 --> 00:24:04.250
He begged me.

403
00:24:04.930 --> 00:24:06.932
I didn't listen.

404
00:24:11.817 --> 00:24:13.819
When?

405
00:24:15.581 --> 00:24:17.583
What?

406
00:24:19.184 --> 00:24:21.186
When did he ask you to
turn the bus around?

407
00:24:21.907 --> 00:24:23.909
Was it before or after
you saw the tree?

408
00:24:25.391 --> 00:24:27.393
After.

409
00:24:27.953 --> 00:24:30.756
Oh. well. then you
were already screwed.

410
00:24:32.478 --> 00:24:33.998
Apparently. it's once
you see the tree.

411
00:24:34.039 --> 00:24:36.079
that's when
everything. you know.

412
00:24:37.723 --> 00:24:39.563
Yeah. I wouldn't
spend too much time

413
00:24:39.605 --> 00:24:41.607
kicking yourself for that part.

414
00:24:42.528 --> 00:24:44.530
Those people.

415
00:24:44.890 --> 00:24:47.371
They got on my bus.

416
00:24:47.413 --> 00:24:49.493
It was my job to get them
where they were going.

417
00:24:49.535 --> 00:24:50.814
All right. tell me something.

418
00:24:50.856 --> 00:24:54.418
Does your pity party
come with music? Hm?

419
00:24:54.460 --> 00:24:57.060
Will you be serving
finger sandwiches?

420
00:24:57.102 --> 00:24:59.102
Look. it's not your fault!

421
00:24:59.144 --> 00:25:01.146
Okay?

422
00:25:01.507 --> 00:25:03.347
I mean. if you wanna
feel like shit. fine.

423
00:25:03.389 --> 00:25:08.111
but feel like shit 'cause
your life is fucked.

424
00:25:08.153 --> 00:25:09.953
Don't carry around a
bunch of guilt thinking

425
00:25:09.995 --> 00:25:11.355
that you ruined anybody else's.

426
00:25:11.397 --> 00:25:14.199
Besides. no offence...

427
00:25:15.401 --> 00:25:17.403
they were riding a bus.

428
00:25:18.283 --> 00:25:20.483
Their lives couldn't have
been that great to begin with.

429
00:25:23.288 --> 00:25:25.290
It was a bad joke. Sorry.

430
00:25:34.500 --> 00:25:37.062
You know I wasn't even supposed
to be driving that day?

431
00:25:39.184 --> 00:25:41.587
I took that job to
pay for my degree.

432
00:25:43.709 --> 00:25:46.071
Last month I finally
paid off my tuition.

433
00:25:48.033 --> 00:25:51.194
I was all set to hand in
my notice and I thought.

434
00:25:51.236 --> 00:25:53.837
why not stay a few extra weeks?

435
00:25:53.879 --> 00:25:56.602
Put aside something extra
so I can treat myself.

436
00:25:58.003 --> 00:26:00.646
Take a little trip
and celebrate.

437
00:26:02.568 --> 00:26:05.210
I deserve a little
reward. right?

438
00:26:08.253 --> 00:26:10.255
Is this what I deserve?

439
00:26:16.261 --> 00:26:18.263
I sold my company right
before I got here.

440
00:26:20.906 --> 00:26:23.389
Finally achieved the one thing
I worked my whole life for.

441
00:26:27.753 --> 00:26:29.755
To getting what we deserve.

442
00:26:35.841 --> 00:26:37.561
Mm.

443
00:26:39.044 --> 00:26:40.724
Ah. it doesn't get easier.

444
00:26:40.766 --> 00:26:42.768
Yeah.

445
00:26:46.812 --> 00:26:48.814
Jim?

446
00:27:08.233 --> 00:27:10.113
Hi.

447
00:27:10.155 --> 00:27:11.354
Hey.

448
00:27:11.396 --> 00:27:13.398
I'm sorry. I didn't
hear you come in.

449
00:27:14.760 --> 00:27:16.400
Who are you?

450
00:27:16.442 --> 00:27:18.482
I'm Marielle. I
was on the bus.

451
00:27:18.524 --> 00:27:20.526
Oh.

452
00:27:21.166 --> 00:27:22.365
Don't worry. I'm a nurse.

453
00:27:22.407 --> 00:27:25.851
I was just helping Kristi
inventory the supplies.

454
00:27:27.212 --> 00:27:29.214
Um. I'm looking for my husband?

455
00:27:30.255 --> 00:27:32.738
Jim? He left a
little while ago.

456
00:27:34.460 --> 00:27:36.462
Thank you.

457
00:27:39.865 --> 00:27:41.144
This go other storage.

458
00:27:41.186 --> 00:27:43.188
Okay.

459
00:27:44.870 --> 00:27:46.349
Jim.

460
00:27:46.391 --> 00:27:48.393
What are you doing. honey?
You should be resting.

461
00:27:49.715 --> 00:27:51.595
We need to talk.

462
00:27:51.637 --> 00:27:53.236
Okay.

463
00:27:53.278 --> 00:27:54.438
Over here.

464
00:27:54.480 --> 00:27:57.322
Take. take more.
Take more. Yeah.

465
00:27:58.644 --> 00:28:00.646
Jesus.

466
00:28:04.329 --> 00:28:07.290
I laid down there all night
thinking I was gonna die.

467
00:28:07.332 --> 00:28:09.655
and I just kept
asking myself "why?"

468
00:28:11.456 --> 00:28:13.336
Why did that road lead us here?

469
00:28:13.378 --> 00:28:16.219
What the fuck is the
point of all of this?

470
00:28:16.261 --> 00:28:18.782
Whoa. whoa. whoa. you
can't just take this stuff!

471
00:28:18.824 --> 00:28:20.143
It doesn't belong to you!

472
00:28:20.185 --> 00:28:22.187
Hey! You go! Now!

473
00:28:23.188 --> 00:28:25.190
Fucking people.

474
00:28:27.192 --> 00:28:29.112
Fucking vultures.

475
00:28:29.154 --> 00:28:31.597
Did you know Kristi's
fiancee was on that bus?

476
00:28:32.678 --> 00:28:33.757
What?

477
00:28:33.799 --> 00:28:35.639
Yeah.

478
00:28:35.681 --> 00:28:38.401
And what you said about the
wires not being connected?

479
00:28:38.443 --> 00:28:39.483
That's not possible.

480
00:28:39.525 --> 00:28:40.724
No. no. I'm telling you...

481
00:28:40.766 --> 00:28:43.689
Oh. no. it's not that.
I know. I believe you.

482
00:28:45.210 --> 00:28:48.814
It's just that there
is no way that...

483
00:28:51.416 --> 00:28:54.297
When we build a
new rollercoaster.

484
00:28:54.339 --> 00:28:57.380
we design it to do things
that seem impossible.

485
00:28:57.422 --> 00:28:59.102
because the more
impossible it seems.

486
00:28:59.144 --> 00:29:01.827
the stronger the reaction you
get from the people riding it.

487
00:29:03.549 --> 00:29:06.710
I know how this
sounds. but what if...

488
00:29:06.752 --> 00:29:12.435
what if all this was designed
just to see how we react?

489
00:29:12.477 --> 00:29:16.001
I mean. what if this is all some
kind of fucked-up experiment?

490
00:29:19.725 --> 00:29:21.727
The radio worked.

491
00:29:24.249 --> 00:29:25.249
No.

492
00:29:25.290 --> 00:29:27.130
We made contact with someone.

493
00:29:27.172 --> 00:29:29.052
So. then why is everybody
just standing...

494
00:29:29.094 --> 00:29:31.096
'Cause they don't know.

495
00:29:32.698 --> 00:29:34.177
Right as the storm
was coming in.

496
00:29:34.219 --> 00:29:35.899
just as we were about
to wrap things up.

497
00:29:35.941 --> 00:29:39.022
I heard a voice. A man.

498
00:29:39.064 --> 00:29:40.984
That's why I came
running back here.

499
00:29:41.026 --> 00:29:42.786
He-he warned me. Tabitha.

500
00:29:42.828 --> 00:29:46.149
Or threatened me.
I don't know which.

501
00:29:46.191 --> 00:29:48.111
but he knew my name.

502
00:29:48.153 --> 00:29:49.753
and he said you
shouldn't be digging.

503
00:29:49.795 --> 00:29:52.317
and then just like that.
our house collapsed.

504
00:29:54.239 --> 00:29:56.241
You think someone's watching us?

505
00:29:56.722 --> 00:29:57.761
All I know is...

506
00:29:57.803 --> 00:29:59.805
Honey.

507
00:30:01.767 --> 00:30:03.769
All I know is

508
00:30:04.209 --> 00:30:06.009
someone got on the
other end of that radio

509
00:30:06.051 --> 00:30:08.053
and they talked to me.

510
00:30:08.614 --> 00:30:10.616
Over there.

511
00:30:11.536 --> 00:30:13.538
Did anyone else hear it?

512
00:30:14.499 --> 00:30:16.501
The voice on the radio?

513
00:30:34.199 --> 00:30:36.201
It's your move. Boyd...

514
00:30:37.562 --> 00:30:39.564
but I gotta say...

515
00:30:40.926 --> 00:30:42.928
your options don't look great.

516
00:30:44.970 --> 00:30:46.972
This ain't real.

517
00:30:48.453 --> 00:30:50.974
You're not here.

518
00:30:51.016 --> 00:30:53.056
You wanna talk about what
can and can't be real?

519
00:30:53.098 --> 00:30:55.100
That's the part
you wanna focus on?

520
00:30:57.262 --> 00:30:59.382
Yeah. I don't know.

521
00:30:59.424 --> 00:31:01.384
I got a little mystery boy

522
00:31:01.426 --> 00:31:04.387
sending people through
magic trees in the forest.

523
00:31:04.429 --> 00:31:05.869
my hand's not shaking anymore.

524
00:31:05.911 --> 00:31:09.152
but now I got fucking worms
underneath my skin. So. yeah.

525
00:31:09.194 --> 00:31:11.356
yeah. maybe that's the
part we should talk about!

526
00:31:14.279 --> 00:31:18.083
Or... how 'bout we talk about
what's really on your mind?

527
00:31:20.525 --> 00:31:23.648
How exactly are you gonna tell
Kenny that Sara killed his dad?

528
00:31:24.730 --> 00:31:26.249
She didn't kill him.

529
00:31:26.291 --> 00:31:28.451
She opened the door.
Potato. pot-ah-to.

530
00:31:28.493 --> 00:31:29.871
You think Kenny's
gonna be interested

531
00:31:29.895 --> 00:31:31.897
in the minutiae of
exactly what happened?

532
00:31:36.621 --> 00:31:38.623
Let me ask you something.

533
00:31:40.746 --> 00:31:42.748
What benefit is there
in Kenny knowing?

534
00:31:44.549 --> 00:31:46.549
That you lied to him.
You betrayed him.

535
00:31:46.591 --> 00:31:49.472
I didn't... You found out the
